// Semantic direction:
// sikkerhet_sandkasse confines untrusted code to a restricted execution environment.
// capability_system grants specific capabilities rather than granting broad permissions.
// cap_attenuér creates a capability with fewer permissions than the source — never more.
// cap_delegér passes a capability to another process; the recipient is limited to what the delegator holds.
// cap_forening combines permissions from two capabilities; cap_snitt takes only the intersection.
// wasm_sandkasse_vm runs WebAssembly as an isolation boundary with wasm_minne_isolert.
// wasm_import_filter controls which host functions the Wasm module may call.
// seccomp_profil whitelists allowed syscalls at the kernel level for Linux sandboxes.
// syscall_brudd terminates the sandboxed process when a forbidden syscall is attempted.
// navnerom_isolasjon (Linux namespaces) isolates the process's view of the system.
// pid_navnerom hides other processes from the sandbox; nett_navnerom gives a separate network stack.
// cgroup_v2 enforces cpu_kvote and minne_kvote at the kernel resource controller level.
// melding_validér checks that sandkasse_melding payloads conform to the allowed schema.
// audit_logg_sandkasse records every capability use for security forensics.

// Primitive flow:
// opprett sandkasse: sandkasse_konfig{caps: [cap_fil_les("/data"), cap_nett_utgående]}
//   -> navnerom_opprett (pid, nett, fil) -> cgroup_v2 (cpu=50%, minne=128MB)
//   -> seccomp_profil(tillatte: [read, write, mmap, exit]) -> sandkasse klar
// kjør kode: wasm_instans_sikkert(bytekode) -> wasm_import_filter
//   -> kode forsøker å lese /etc/passwd -> cap_fil_les("/data") match? -> NEI
//   -> syscall_brudd -> audit_hendelse{brudd, /etc/passwd} -> avslutt sandkasse
// capability delegasjon: tjeneste A har cap_nett_utgående
//   -> cap_attenuér: lag cap med kun port 443 tillatt
//   -> cap_delegér til tjeneste B -> B kan kun nå port 443

// This defines the security sandbox: capability-based access control, WASM isolation,
// Linux namespaces, seccomp syscall filtering, cgroup resource limits, and audit logging.
